ed by: §III-A.\n474\t\n475\t[13]\n476\tN. Ryant, P. Singh, V. Krishnamohan, R. Varma, K. Church, C. Cieri, J. Du, S. Ganapathy, and M. Liberman (2020)\n477\t\n478\tThe third dihard diarization challenge.\n479\t\n480\tarXiv preprint arXiv:2012.01477.\n481\t\n482\tCited by: §III-A.\n483\t\n484\t[14]\n485\tX. Shi, X. Wang, Z. Guo, Y. Wang, P. Zhang, X. Zhang, Z. Guo, H. Hao, Y. Xi, B. Yang, et al. (2026)\n486\t\n487\tQwen3-asr technical report.\n488\t\n489\tarXiv preprint arXiv:2601.21337.\n490\t\n491\tCited by: §III-E.\n492\t\n493\t[15]\n494\tSmartGlasses Challenge Organizers (2026)\n495\t\n496\tSmartGlasses Challenge 2026: egocentric speech interaction on AI glasses.\n497\t\n498\tNote: https://aslp-lab.github.io/SmartGlasses/Accessed: 2026-07-01\n499\t\n500\tCited by: §I,\n501\t§I.\n502\t\n503\t[16]\n504\tA. Vinnikov, A. Ivry, A. Hurvitz, I. Abramovski, S. Koubi, I. Gurvich, S. Peer, X. Xiao, B. M. Elizalde, N. Kanda, et al. (2024)\n505\t\n506\tNOTSOFAR-1 challenge: new datasets, baseline, and tasks for distant meeting transcription.\n507\t\n508\tarXiv preprint arXiv:2401.08887.\n509\t\n510\tCited by: §III-A.\n511\t\n512\t[17]\n513\tT. von Neumann, C. Boeddeker, M. Delcroix, and R. Haeb-Umbach (2023)\n514\t\n515\tMeetEval: a toolkit for computation of word error rates for meeting transcription systems.\n516\t\n517\tIn Proc. 7th International Workshop on Speech Processing in Everyday Environments (CHiME 2023),\n518\t\n519\t pp. 27–32.\n520\t\n521\tExternal Links: Document\n522\t\n523\tCited by: §II.\n524\t\n525\t[18]\n526\tQ. Wang, W. Wang, K. Chen, J. Yang, Y. Wang, S. Niu, C. Zhang, J. Du, and C. Lee (2024)\n527\t\n528\tWeSep: a scalable and flexible toolkit towards generalizable target speaker extraction.\n529\t\n530\tarXiv preprint arXiv:2409.15799.\n531\t\n532\tCited by: §I,\n533\t§III-C.\n534\t\n535\t[19]\n536\tK. Xu, Y. Jia, K. Huang, J. Chen, W. Li, K. Liu, F. Xie, X. Tang, and Y. Hu (2026)\n537\t\n538\tFireredasr2s: a state-of-the-art industrial-grade all-in-